 Qumbu - The Qumbu Stock Theft Unit (STU) together with Mbizana STU, Maluti STU, Mthatha STU, accompanied by the OR Tambo District Vispol members conducted an anti-stock theft operation on Thursday, which resulted to 54 sheep being recovered and two persons arrested. "Two suspects, aged between 22 -33 years, from Sulenkama, were arrested and charged for stock theft after they were found in possession of the 54 sheep," said police spokesperson, Brigadier Thembinkosi Kinana. "Fourteen out of the 54 sheep were positively identified by the complainant and owner. "The suspects are expected to appear before the Qumbu Magistrate's Court on Friday." Another 48 goats were recovered at Etwa and are impounded at Qumbu pound. "Anyone with missing goats is invited to come and identify them." Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Lt Gen Liziwe Ntshinga, welcomed the success and collaboration between various units. "We must combine strategies, resources and coordinate efforts to thwart stock theft activities at all cost," said the Provincial Commissioner Lt Gen Ntshinga. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 